# Compression Pipeline Workflow

- Work meticulously and do not rush. Read the relevant plan, tests, and implementation before making changes.
- Use bounded loops with concrete verifiers. Stop when tests pass, benchmark sweeps finish, or the max iteration count is reached.
- If an API key, SDK install, package choice, account access, rate-limit decision, or other user-provided input is needed, pause the loop and ask the user instead of guessing.
- When adding or using a library/package, prefer the latest stable version. Verify the package name, current stable release, and official usage instead of guessing or choosing outdated versions.
- Verify one real Token Company API call manually before automating loops against the hosted API.
- Keep `.env` out of git. Do not commit secrets, API keys, tokens, credentials, or local config.
- Ensure `.env` is listed in `.gitignore` before any commit or PR work.
- The compression layer must never throw into the live course-generation path. On compression failure, return original input with fallback stats. On empty input, return empty output with zeroed stats and do not call the API.
